1
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:07,333
After twenty days of continuous bombing,

2
00:02:07,583 --> 00:02:10,003
Nanking finally fell to the Japanese.

3
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:13,040
It was December the 13th, 1937.

4
00:02:13,583 --> 00:02:14,373
I remember

5
00:02:14,583 --> 00:02:16,083
everyone was running that day,

6
00:02:16,541 --> 00:02:18,711
but no one could escape that heavy fog.

7
00:02:24,125 --> 00:02:25,575
Major Li only had a few men left.

8
00:02:25,791 --> 00:02:28,461
Nanking was no longer able to put up a fight,

9
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:30,751
and those left behind, ran for their lives.

10
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,170
Stop counting.

11
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:01,833
Shu and two others are missing.

12
00:03:40,291 --> 00:03:41,791
Let us in!

13
00:03:41,958 --> 00:03:43,418
There's no room!

14
00:03:43,583 --> 00:03:45,503
Find your own place to hide!

15
00:03:46,291 --> 00:03:47,331
I said, there's no more room!

16
00:03:48,666 --> 00:03:49,286
Let's go.

17
00:04:02,791 --> 00:04:03,831
Keep going!

18
00:04:15,875 --> 00:04:18,995
Hey.

19
00:04:19,958 --> 00:04:20,918
There are people inside.

20
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:21,923
Who is there?

21
00:04:22,208 --> 00:04:25,618
Come out!

22
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:32,248
Bastards!

23
00:04:34,416 --> 00:04:35,456
Go to hell!

24
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:34,075
Stop!

25
00:05:36,458 --> 00:05:43,998
Turn around!

26
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,120
Don't move!

27
00:05:52,125 --> 00:05:52,995
American.

28
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:54,080
From the refuge.

29
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:54,790
What?

30
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,080
American.

31
00:05:56,958 --> 00:05:57,788
Not soldier.

32
00:06:04,458 --> 00:06:05,368
John Miller.

33
00:06:05,541 --> 00:06:06,541
Raise your hands!

34
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:07,923
Working at the church.

35
00:06:08,291 --> 00:06:09,291
Raise your hands!

36
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:12,615
I said raise your hands!

37
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:46,003
Separated...

38
00:06:46,916 --> 00:06:49,366
You separated from your families?

39
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,460
You...

40
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:55,075
families...

41
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:56,416
separated?

42
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:58,868
I'm...

43
00:06:59,458 --> 00:07:00,078
going to...

44
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,293
Winchester Cathedral.

45
00:07:04,958 --> 00:07:05,868
You know where it is?

46
00:07:07,375 --> 00:07:09,075
Where?

47
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:21,083
Mister.

48
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:22,333
Did you say...

49
00:07:23,458 --> 00:07:24,538
Did you say "mister?"

50
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:25,745
Who said "mister?"

51
00:07:26,791 --> 00:07:27,711
You speak English?

52
00:07:28,083 --> 00:07:30,963
We are from Winchester Cathedral.

53
00:07:32,083 --> 00:07:33,003
Say that again.

54
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:36,541
We are from Winchester Cathedral.

55
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:40,076
You're kidding?

56
00:07:40,708 --> 00:07:42,618
We are students at the convent.

57
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:44,250
You going there?

58
00:07:45,416 --> 00:07:46,786
Why do you want to go there?

59
00:07:48,875 --> 00:07:50,415
I'm helping to bury your father.

60
00:07:51,416 --> 00:07:53,416
Well, not your father father...

61
00:07:53,583 --> 00:07:54,253
Father Ingleman.

62
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:55,366
Father Ingleman, yeah.

63
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,080
I'm helping burying him.

64
00:07:57,916 --> 00:07:59,916
Father Ingleman, I'm sending him off...

65
00:08:01,708 --> 00:08:03,118
to heaven or wherever.

66
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:07,790
You show me the way?

67
00:08:47,708 --> 00:08:48,288
Peng,

68
00:08:48,458 --> 00:08:49,498
move to the flank,

69
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:50,290
prepare to engage.

70
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:54,043
Damn it, are you deaf?

71
00:08:54,291 --> 00:08:54,961
Major Li,

72
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:57,293
we are the last ones left.

73
00:08:57,916 --> 00:08:59,286
We should leave the city now.

74
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:02,208
Keep fighting.

75
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:03,250
Yes sir.

76
00:09:22,166 --> 00:09:23,416
Got you!

77
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:16,713
Let's go.

78
00:10:16,875 --> 00:10:17,415
Yes sir.

79
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:27,500
That way!

80
00:11:04,291 --> 00:11:05,871
Up there, on the right!

81
00:11:47,583 --> 00:11:48,963
On the left! Fire!

82
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:24,788
Cover them!

83
00:12:46,875 --> 00:12:49,325
The Chinese army didn't have adequate weapons

84
00:12:49,583 --> 00:12:51,253
to destroy the enemy's tanks,

85
00:12:51,416 --> 00:12:52,996
so they employed a tactic from ancient warfare.

86
00:12:53,541 --> 00:12:55,371
They formed a human shield

87
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:57,673
to get a bomb close to the tanks.

88
00:12:58,291 --> 00:12:59,501
At the time, the Chinese people

89
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:01,960
couldn't bear the thought of losing their country,

90
00:13:02,291 --> 00:13:03,871
and such selfless acts were not uncommon.

91
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,120
Zhen!

92
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:26,290
Let me go!

93
00:16:29,166 --> 00:16:29,996
Zhen!

94
00:16:34,916 --> 00:16:35,456
Come on!

95
00:17:04,791 --> 00:17:05,831
Father Ingleman...

96
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:07,043
fly away.

97
00:17:07,375 --> 00:17:08,075
Fly away?

98
00:17:09,375 --> 00:17:12,115
On here, Japanese, bomb.

99
00:17:13,375 --> 00:17:15,115
- He flew away with the bomb, right.
- Yes.

100
00:17:15,791 --> 00:17:18,291
Why was the deceased out here?

101
00:17:18,666 --> 00:17:20,786
- Gu. All because of Gu.
- Gu?

102
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:22,828
He said, bad smell.

103
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:25,330
He moved the body here.

104
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:26,330
Who's Gu?

105
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:28,456
Gu is our cook.

106
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:30,003
He ran away.

107
00:17:30,208 --> 00:17:31,788
He leaves some students here.

108
00:17:31,958 --> 00:17:34,368
Some students took away by parents.

109
00:17:34,958 --> 00:17:36,998
Some students nowhere to go.

110
00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:40,423
So who's inside?

111
00:17:41,125 --> 00:17:41,915
Just you and the girls?

112
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:43,830
Just you and the girls.

113
00:17:47,375 --> 00:17:48,455
Even without a body,

114
00:17:49,375 --> 00:17:50,245
you gotta pay me.

115
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:51,330
No.

116
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:53,870
No... You gotta pay me.

117
00:17:54,041 --> 00:17:54,501
No.

118
00:17:55,291 --> 00:17:56,081
That's the rule.

119
00:17:56,708 --> 00:17:57,998
There's nothing I can do about it.

120
00:17:58,708 --> 00:17:59,498
With what I came through,

121
00:17:59,708 --> 00:18:00,998
I should raise the price.

122
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:02,423
So is the money inside?

123
00:18:02,583 --> 00:18:03,373
No. No money.

124
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:04,921
Money? Inside?

125
00:18:05,583 --> 00:18:06,173
No.

126
00:18:06,458 --> 00:18:07,208
Come on.

127
00:18:07,541 --> 00:18:08,751
There's no money inside?

128
00:18:08,916 --> 00:18:09,326
No.

129
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:10,080
Let's look.

130
00:18:10,541 --> 00:18:11,671
It's a Catholic church.

131
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,253
There's gotta be some cash inside.

132
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:13,996
No.

133
00:18:14,291 --> 00:18:14,921
No?

134
00:18:15,083 --> 00:18:16,373
You say anything but no?

135
00:18:18,125 --> 00:18:19,535
Can you fix truck?

136
00:18:21,708 --> 00:18:22,498
Help us.

137
00:18:23,125 --> 00:18:24,115
Leave Nanking.

138
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:25,210
Fix this truck?

139
00:18:26,625 --> 00:18:27,245
For free?

140
00:18:28,708 --> 00:18:29,288
No.

141
00:18:30,666 --> 00:18:32,206
I can take parts, sell parts.

142
00:18:32,375 --> 00:18:33,205
You got tools?

143
00:18:33,875 --> 00:18:34,495
No.

144
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:35,920
Let's get inside.

145
00:18:40,041 --> 00:18:41,581
Zhen didn't even make a noise.

146
00:18:42,041 --> 00:18:43,541
Even when they stabbed her over and over,

147
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:46,366
yet she didn't make a noise.

148
00:18:50,416 --> 00:18:51,786
It's all my fault.

149
00:18:53,375 --> 00:18:54,415
It's not your fault.

150
00:18:54,916 --> 00:18:56,326
It is your fault.

151
00:18:57,666 --> 00:18:59,416
Your father promised to take us

152
00:18:59,583 --> 00:19:02,003
on a boat and leave Nanking.

153
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:03,040
Where is he?

154
00:19:03,416 --> 00:19:04,666
He ran off.

155
00:19:05,083 --> 00:19:06,373
We waited and waited

156
00:19:06,791 --> 00:19:08,791
and now the Japanese are here.

157
00:19:09,041 --> 00:19:10,791
Now the Japanese are everywhere,

158
00:19:10,958 --> 00:19:13,038
and it's too late to go to the refuge.

159
00:19:15,583 --> 00:19:17,543
Zhen died because of your father!

160
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:20,080
Shut up!

161
00:19:22,083 --> 00:19:23,793
What are you doing?

162
00:19:24,583 --> 00:19:26,003
Stop!

163
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:27,960
Stop fighting!

164
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:29,825
Hey.

165
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:33,541
Hey! Stop!

166
00:19:34,708 --> 00:19:35,368
Stop!

167
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,710
I'm John. Hi.

168
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:43,460
I'm American.

169
00:19:44,083 --> 00:19:45,623
He's the mortician for Father's funeral.

170
00:19:50,458 --> 00:19:51,578
I know it's hard.

171
00:19:52,125 --> 00:19:53,955
But you've gotta stop fighting everybody.

172
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:56,370
You know you two... you've seen enough...

173
00:19:56,750 --> 00:19:59,290
seen enough tragedy for a lifetime today.

174
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:08,206
I can't... um...

175
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:10,003
I'm not good with kids.

176
00:20:10,166 --> 00:20:10,996
Let's go.

177
00:20:11,708 --> 00:20:14,078
You want some flour? You like some flour?

178
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:16,830
- Make some bread for the girls.
- Buns.

179
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:18,710
Buns.

180
00:20:18,875 --> 00:20:19,865
Buns, whatever.

181
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,670
Let's go find the collection box.

182
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:28,463
Where?

183
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:30,041
- Upstairs?
- No.

184
00:20:34,541 --> 00:20:35,501
Oh, nice.

185
00:20:36,541 --> 00:20:38,081
Forget going back to the refuge,

186
00:20:38,250 --> 00:20:40,330
I think I'm bunking here tonight.

187
00:20:45,791 --> 00:20:47,371
He's grim, who's that?

188
00:20:49,875 --> 00:20:50,915
Is that Father Ingleman?

189
00:20:51,125 --> 00:20:51,705
Yes.

190
00:20:52,250 --> 00:20:54,080
These North Europeans they're all like,

191
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:56,500
you know, tuna, playwrights,

192
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:58,080
not much fun.

193
00:20:58,708 --> 00:20:59,918
Look at that face,

194
00:21:00,083 --> 00:21:02,873
he's ruining the...

195
00:21:03,708 --> 00:21:05,788
What do you call it? Feng... Fengshui?

196
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:09,368
I can't have a priest staring at me

197
00:21:09,583 --> 00:21:11,713
- while I'm sleeping.
- No...

198
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:13,870
My father.

199
00:21:16,625 --> 00:21:17,205
Me...

200
00:21:18,375 --> 00:21:19,365
orphan...

201
00:21:19,916 --> 00:21:20,786
adopted.

202
00:21:21,125 --> 00:21:21,705
I'm sorry.

203
00:21:21,916 --> 00:21:22,786
But I just...

204
00:21:23,708 --> 00:21:25,958
It's not good for me to have a priest

205
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:27,915
staring at me while I'm sleeping.

206
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:29,000
I can't.

207
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:32,785
Please, I gotta just... there, better.

208
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:34,788
You got any drink around here?

209
00:21:34,958 --> 00:21:35,538
No.

210
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:37,920
You're a church. You got wine, something?

211
00:21:38,083 --> 00:21:38,673
Nothing.

212
00:21:39,041 --> 00:21:39,671
Nothing?

213
00:21:48,708 --> 00:21:51,078
- No.
- No, no...

214
00:21:51,958 --> 00:21:53,248
That's a shaving kit.

215
00:21:54,625 --> 00:21:55,575
What a jerk!

216
00:21:57,041 --> 00:21:58,211
I said you are a jerk!

217
00:21:59,791 --> 00:22:00,921
What did you say your name was?

218
00:22:01,750 --> 00:22:02,580
George Chen.

219
00:22:03,125 --> 00:22:03,915
George.

220
00:22:04,416 --> 00:22:05,246
Tomorrow,

221
00:22:06,416 --> 00:22:07,576
you fix truck,

222
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:09,463
help us.

223
00:22:11,750 --> 00:22:12,500
Fix truck?

224
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:15,373
No money!

225
00:22:17,041 --> 00:22:18,001
Money, George.

226
00:22:24,208 --> 00:22:24,788
Gu.

227
00:22:24,958 --> 00:22:26,748
Open the door, it's Ling.

228
00:22:27,125 --> 00:22:28,035
Can you hear me

229
00:22:29,625 --> 00:22:30,955
Gu.

230
00:22:31,125 --> 00:22:31,995
Open up.

231
00:22:32,833 --> 00:22:34,003
It's Ling.

232
00:22:34,416 --> 00:22:35,496
Did you really make a deal with him?

233
00:22:35,666 --> 00:22:36,366
Of course.

234
00:22:36,541 --> 00:22:38,001
Otherwise I wouldn't have brought you here.

235
00:22:38,458 --> 00:22:40,618
Gu.

236
00:22:40,791 --> 00:22:42,081
Open the door, it's Ling.

237
00:22:42,250 --> 00:22:44,000
Gu, have you gone deaf?

238
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,330
Someone's here.

239
00:22:46,500 --> 00:22:47,790
Where's Gu? Ask him to come out.

240
00:22:47,958 --> 00:22:49,118
Go to the refuge on the west side.

241
00:22:49,291 --> 00:22:51,121
Leave now, go to the refuge.

242
00:22:51,291 --> 00:22:53,291
No, we're here for Gu.

243
00:22:53,458 --> 00:22:54,288
Gu's not here.

244
00:22:54,458 --> 00:22:55,618
Bullshit! Get out of my way!

245
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:56,670
Gu told me,

246
00:22:56,833 --> 00:22:58,463
this church is under Western protection.

247
00:22:58,625 --> 00:22:59,955
The Japanese can't come in.

248
00:23:00,125 --> 00:23:02,325
Bastard! I served Gu all night for free,

249
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:03,500
he promised to let us stay.

250
00:23:03,666 --> 00:23:04,706
Ask that bastard Gu to come out!

251
00:23:04,875 --> 00:23:05,615
He's really not here.

252
00:23:05,791 --> 00:23:06,291
How come?

253
00:23:06,458 --> 00:23:07,618
He ran off this morning.

254
00:23:07,833 --> 00:23:09,333
You should go to the refuge.

255
00:23:29,875 --> 00:23:30,785
We're not leaving.

256
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:47,368
Hey! How dare you!

257
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:49,210
Hurry.

258
00:23:49,375 --> 00:23:50,495
Go to the refuge!

259
00:23:50,916 --> 00:23:51,746
To the refuge!

260
00:23:51,916 --> 00:23:54,036
The refuge doesn't even
have space left for maggots.

261
00:23:54,208 --> 00:23:56,868
Please, have some mercy and let us in.

262
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:00,830
Don't jump.

263
00:24:26,125 --> 00:24:27,535
They're from the red-light district.

264
00:24:27,791 --> 00:24:28,831
What's that?

265
00:24:29,166 --> 00:24:30,416
It means brothel.

266
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:39,250
They were the famous women of the Qin Huai River.

267
00:24:39,583 --> 00:24:40,963
The myths surrounding them

268
00:24:41,291 --> 00:24:43,581
were as ancient as the city of Nanking.

269
00:24:51,458 --> 00:24:53,418
That's a Westerner!

270
00:24:53,708 --> 00:24:54,418
Is he a priest?

271
00:24:54,583 --> 00:24:55,713
No way.

272
00:24:55,875 --> 00:24:57,415
What kind of priest would be such a flirt?

273
00:24:57,583 --> 00:24:58,583
Who cares,

274
00:24:58,750 --> 00:25:00,210
as long as he can protect us.

275
00:25:00,375 --> 00:25:01,245
True.

276
00:25:36,083 --> 00:25:37,173
Come up here.

277
00:25:38,083 --> 00:25:42,043
This was stolen from the bowels of hell.

278
00:25:42,458 --> 00:25:44,578
Long time not make bread.

279
00:25:44,750 --> 00:25:47,000
Long time not make bread? No bread?

280
00:25:47,416 --> 00:25:49,326
Not tonight, tonight we're having bread.

281
00:25:52,708 --> 00:25:55,288
These women quickly took over the cellar.

282
00:25:55,666 --> 00:25:57,786
It was once a filthy, messy place,

283
00:25:58,208 --> 00:25:59,708
but within hours,

284
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,790
they had transformed it into the Qin Huai River.

285
00:26:02,208 --> 00:26:03,368
The fragrance of rouge and perfume

286
00:26:03,541 --> 00:26:05,251
danced up through the air.

287
00:26:27,250 --> 00:26:28,250
I can smell the bread.

288
00:26:28,375 --> 00:26:29,415
We are coming up!

289
00:26:42,250 --> 00:26:43,870
I couldn't stop them.

290
00:26:47,833 --> 00:26:48,543
Hello.

291
00:26:52,333 --> 00:26:53,503
I remember

292
00:26:53,875 --> 00:26:56,075
when I first saw these women,

293
