580
00:53:10,458 --> 00:53:11,868
Keep firing!

581
00:53:59,875 --> 00:54:00,955
Hold your fire!

582
00:54:47,583 --> 00:54:48,253
Wait!

583
00:55:12,958 --> 00:55:13,578
Fire!

584
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:00,580
First platoon to the back gate!

585
00:56:01,166 --> 00:56:02,996
Second platoon to the front gate!

586
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:10,790
Colonel,

587
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:13,250
he used to work for the traffic department.

588
00:56:13,750 --> 00:56:15,250
Most roads in Nanking are destroyed.

589
00:56:15,416 --> 00:56:16,786
Having him can be useful.

590
00:56:17,666 --> 00:56:18,666
Speak Japanese?

591
00:56:18,833 --> 00:56:19,423
Yes.

592
00:56:49,291 --> 00:56:51,291
Were our soldiers here recently?

593
00:56:53,208 --> 00:56:54,668
Are you the resident priest?

594
00:56:57,125 --> 00:56:57,665
Yes.

595
00:56:57,833 --> 00:56:58,373
Father,

596
00:56:58,750 --> 00:57:01,210
I apologize on behalf of our soldiers.

597
00:57:01,708 --> 00:57:02,788
Please understand.

598
00:57:03,083 --> 00:57:04,373
In the middle of a war,

599
00:57:04,708 --> 00:57:07,538
occasional unfortunate behavior is inevitable.

600
00:57:10,083 --> 00:57:10,873
Your church

601
00:57:11,041 --> 00:57:12,421
is very beautiful.

602
00:57:14,500 --> 00:57:15,290
How do you do?

603
00:57:16,708 --> 00:57:18,418
Are you students here at the convent?

604
00:57:19,083 --> 00:57:20,503
So sorry to have caused you alarm.

605
00:57:20,666 --> 00:57:21,206
Please...

606
00:57:22,416 --> 00:57:24,076
don't hurt the children anymore.

607
00:57:24,458 --> 00:57:25,168
Naturally.

608
00:57:25,541 --> 00:57:26,871
My name is Hasegawa.

609
00:57:27,291 --> 00:57:29,831
I am responsible for the safety of this area.

610
00:57:30,208 --> 00:57:31,368
Please do not worry...

611
00:57:32,083 --> 00:57:33,713
about the security of the church

612
00:57:33,875 --> 00:57:34,705
and the students.

613
00:57:36,375 --> 00:57:37,535
I apologize...

614
00:57:38,208 --> 00:57:42,418
but I have no confidence... in that assurance.

615
00:57:42,791 --> 00:57:44,461
My guarantee is effective.

616
00:57:44,958 --> 00:57:45,868
From now on,

617
00:57:46,583 --> 00:57:48,753
I shall post armed guards in front of the church

618
00:57:48,916 --> 00:57:50,206
to protect you all.

619
00:57:58,916 --> 00:58:00,416
There is not a lot of food

620
00:58:00,583 --> 00:58:02,043
in Nanking at the moment.

621
00:58:02,708 --> 00:58:05,118
I hope the students will not go hungry.

622
00:58:14,791 --> 00:58:15,421
May I?

623
00:59:13,250 --> 00:59:13,790
Thank you.

624
00:59:15,666 --> 00:59:16,536
Did you like it?

625
00:59:19,125 --> 00:59:21,205
This is a Japanese folk song,

626
00:59:21,666 --> 00:59:22,456
"My Home."

627
00:59:23,333 --> 00:59:24,793
It is about hills and rabbits,

628
00:59:24,958 --> 00:59:26,618
and streams full of fish.

629
00:59:27,208 --> 00:59:29,498
It is the most beautiful song in the world

630
00:59:29,666 --> 00:59:31,166
for those who are homesick.

631
00:59:39,666 --> 00:59:41,286
Do the students sing well?

632
00:59:45,208 --> 00:59:46,868
Very well, yes.

633
00:59:47,333 --> 00:59:48,123
That's good.

634
00:59:48,583 --> 00:59:49,333
I shall come back

635
00:59:49,500 --> 00:59:51,080
in a couple of days to hear them.

636
00:59:52,916 --> 00:59:53,536
Why?

637
00:59:53,958 --> 00:59:54,828
No reason.

638
00:59:56,250 --> 00:59:57,870
I happen to love music.

639
00:59:58,416 --> 01:00:00,706
Father, we shall meet again soon.

640
01:00:42,083 --> 01:00:45,923
I hope you will not be lonely buried together.

641
01:01:11,125 --> 01:01:12,075
Father John.

642
01:01:14,125 --> 01:01:16,785
You won't leave us, will you?

643
01:01:32,291 --> 01:01:34,041
We shouldn't have taken over your cellar.

644
01:01:34,500 --> 01:01:35,250
Sorry.

645
01:01:39,291 --> 01:01:40,961
If we hadn't fought with that girl,

646
01:01:41,125 --> 01:01:42,325
she would still be alive.

647
01:01:42,708 --> 01:01:43,918
This is all our fault.

648
01:01:53,625 --> 01:01:54,415
Thank you.

649
01:02:06,208 --> 01:02:08,208
Why not answer Shu?

650
01:02:13,000 --> 01:02:14,420
She called me Father John.

651
01:02:15,333 --> 01:02:16,503
We all need you.

652
01:02:16,666 --> 01:02:17,786
I'm a mortician.

653
01:02:18,708 --> 01:02:19,708
You are priest.

654
01:02:19,875 --> 01:02:20,705
No.

655
01:02:22,000 --> 01:02:23,170
- If we have a priest...
- George.

656
01:02:23,333 --> 01:02:25,503
Maybe Japanese...

657
01:02:25,791 --> 01:02:27,081
not dare...

658
01:02:27,833 --> 01:02:28,583
You are priest!

659
01:02:28,750 --> 01:02:30,120
George, I'm not.

660
01:02:31,833 --> 01:02:33,003
I'm not a priest.

661
01:02:33,166 --> 01:02:33,616
I'm not!

662
01:02:33,791 --> 01:02:35,081
I stayed here,

663
01:02:35,416 --> 01:02:38,116
because I was looking for your cash.

664
01:02:39,208 --> 01:02:41,078
And because that's the nicest bed that

665
01:02:41,250 --> 01:02:42,710
I've slept in in years. I didn't get there.

666
01:02:42,875 --> 01:02:45,115
But is that like a priest? I'm not a priest!

667
01:02:45,875 --> 01:02:46,455
I'm not.

668
01:02:46,625 --> 01:02:49,615
I took catechism lessons as a kid.

669
01:02:49,791 --> 01:02:52,461
Sometimes I remember that when I'm drunk,

670
01:02:52,625 --> 01:02:54,495
which I am as often as I can be.

671
01:03:02,875 --> 01:03:04,665
You not be priest.

672
01:03:05,750 --> 01:03:08,040
Tell girls yourself.

673
01:03:28,125 --> 01:03:29,615
You little shit!

674
01:03:32,208 --> 01:03:32,998
You are.

675
01:03:50,916 --> 01:03:52,826
We've heard about what happen today.

676
01:03:53,375 --> 01:03:54,455
So you're staying?

677
01:04:02,875 --> 01:04:03,495
Yeah.

678
01:04:05,083 --> 01:04:05,713
Even though you were

679
01:04:05,875 --> 01:04:07,495
a drunk bastard last night,

680
01:04:07,625 --> 01:04:09,575
what you did today makes you a hero.

681
01:04:15,291 --> 01:04:17,081
I'm sorry about last night.

682
01:04:19,875 --> 01:04:20,495
Yeah.

683
01:04:22,875 --> 01:04:24,575
I can't leave them by themselves.

684
01:04:25,625 --> 01:04:26,285
And that little shit

685
01:04:26,458 --> 01:04:28,828
has a way of just... you know.

686
01:04:31,416 --> 01:04:33,496
What do you think the Japanese are up to?

687
01:04:34,125 --> 01:04:36,415
Are they really here to protect the students?

688
01:04:42,833 --> 01:04:44,083
We were counting on having you

689
01:04:44,250 --> 01:04:45,540
help us leave Nanking.

690
01:04:45,708 --> 01:04:47,328
But I guess now you'll have to

691
01:04:47,541 --> 01:04:49,421
stay here and be a priest.

692
01:04:51,041 --> 01:04:52,791
Yeah, right.

693
01:04:54,791 --> 01:04:55,461
Priest.

694
01:04:59,125 --> 01:05:00,535
Actually, I came to tell you,

695
01:05:00,666 --> 01:05:02,166
our offer is still good.

696
01:05:02,333 --> 01:05:04,253
We still want you to help us escape.

697
01:05:04,458 --> 01:05:06,668
As soon as the Japanese guards are gone.

698
01:05:08,166 --> 01:05:10,076
Just now the ladies were having a bet.

699
01:05:10,708 --> 01:05:13,168
They said that hero or no hero,

700
01:05:13,375 --> 01:05:14,365
you don't stand a chance

701
01:05:14,541 --> 01:05:16,921
when you're up against a beauty like me.

702
01:05:17,500 --> 01:05:19,120
Don't flatter yourself.

703
01:05:20,583 --> 01:05:21,333
We'll see.

704
01:05:50,916 --> 01:05:51,866
Did you like it?

705
01:05:55,208 --> 01:05:56,208
I only have one string.

706
01:05:56,375 --> 01:05:58,245
It sound like a beggar's plea. Even worse.

707
01:06:08,166 --> 01:06:09,206
You're Pu Sheng.

708
01:06:09,375 --> 01:06:10,245
Born in the Pu region?

709
01:06:11,583 --> 01:06:12,833
My family is also from there.

710
01:06:14,083 --> 01:06:14,923
When you're healthy,

711
01:06:15,208 --> 01:06:16,618
I'll take you to the biggest dance hall,

712
01:06:16,791 --> 01:06:18,121
to see the prettiest girls.

713
01:06:19,791 --> 01:06:20,541
Thank you.

714
01:06:22,208 --> 01:06:22,958
Little hometown fellow,

715
01:06:23,125 --> 01:06:23,915
don't thank me,

716
01:06:24,083 --> 01:06:24,873
marry me.

717
01:06:29,125 --> 01:06:30,665
I'll work in the fields with you.

718
01:06:32,666 --> 01:06:33,666
I don't have...

719
01:06:34,583 --> 01:06:35,423
fields.

720
01:06:36,208 --> 01:06:37,168
What do you have then?

721
01:06:38,750 --> 01:06:41,080
I don't have anything.

722
01:06:41,541 --> 01:06:43,921
Then I'll play my pipa everyday.

723
01:06:44,375 --> 01:06:46,115
When I play, you hold out a bowl.

724
01:06:46,333 --> 01:06:47,793
We'll beg for food and feed your mom.

725
01:06:49,291 --> 01:06:50,961
I don't have a mother.

726
01:06:51,458 --> 01:06:53,458
Everyone in my family is dead.

727
01:07:57,166 --> 01:07:58,996
If you had just come with me,

728
01:07:59,583 --> 01:08:01,213
this wouldn't have happened.

729
01:08:01,541 --> 01:08:03,461
You were so stubborn,

730
01:08:03,708 --> 01:08:04,958
and wouldn't leave without your classmates.

731
01:08:05,166 --> 01:08:06,166
How could I have gotten

732
01:08:06,333 --> 01:08:07,503
that many boat tickets?

733
01:08:08,541 --> 01:08:09,251
Because of you,

734
01:08:10,000 --> 01:08:11,540
I'm staying in Nanking.

735
01:08:17,250 --> 01:08:17,920
Tell me,

736
01:08:18,083 --> 01:08:19,543
what's this?

737
01:08:20,000 --> 01:08:21,210
Explain to me,

738
01:08:21,458 --> 01:08:23,038
why do you do this?

739
01:08:26,916 --> 01:08:28,036
If I don't do this,

740
01:08:28,416 --> 01:08:29,496
I can't survive.

741
01:08:30,166 --> 01:08:31,866
I'm doing this for you.

742
01:08:32,166 --> 01:08:32,916
You must believe me,

743
01:08:33,083 --> 01:08:34,753
I would never do anything bad.

744
01:08:35,458 --> 01:08:36,118
Daughter,

745
01:08:37,041 --> 01:08:38,331
I will find a way

746
01:08:38,916 --> 01:08:40,036
to get you out of Nanking.

747
01:08:51,291 --> 01:08:52,671
No wonder there were no boat tickets.

748
01:08:52,916 --> 01:08:53,746
Traitor!

749
01:09:27,791 --> 01:09:29,121
You work for the Japanese?

750
01:09:29,291 --> 01:09:30,791
Since I cannot save my country,

751
01:09:30,958 --> 01:09:31,998
cannot save others,

752
01:09:32,166 --> 01:09:33,786
I can only try to save myself.

753
01:09:34,291 --> 01:09:36,461
I'm already doing my best, you know.

754
01:09:36,666 --> 01:09:37,826
Do you think it's easy

755
01:09:38,000 --> 01:09:39,120
working for the Japanese?

756
01:09:39,291 --> 01:09:40,501
It's good you work for the Japanese,

757
01:09:40,666 --> 01:09:41,416
that helps us.

758
01:09:41,583 --> 01:09:43,213
What is your plan for your daughter?

759
01:09:43,791 --> 01:09:44,871
I would like to try,

760
01:09:45,041 --> 01:09:46,871
and use my connections with the Japanese

761
01:09:47,041 --> 01:09:48,961
to get my daughter out of the city.

762
01:09:50,291 --> 01:09:51,291
Not to the refuge?

763
01:09:51,458 --> 01:09:52,248
The refuge?

764
01:09:52,416 --> 01:09:54,116
It's not safe there at all!

765
01:09:57,041 --> 01:09:58,961
What's your plan for the rest of the girls?

766
01:10:03,583 --> 01:10:04,293
Mr. Meng?

767
01:10:06,000 --> 01:10:07,120
I have this truck.

768
01:10:07,291 --> 01:10:09,711
If I can get the right tools,

769
01:10:09,958 --> 01:10:11,708
then maybe I can get it started.

770
01:10:11,875 --> 01:10:12,915
Can you help me?

771
01:10:15,541 --> 01:10:16,671
I have a list here.

772
01:10:17,208 --> 01:10:17,918
Mr. Meng.

773
01:10:18,208 --> 01:10:19,578
I need these tools.

774
01:10:20,166 --> 01:10:21,166
Can you help me get them?

775
01:10:22,125 --> 01:10:23,865
You're the only one who can get them for me.

776
01:10:25,083 --> 01:10:31,333
I need these tools.

777
01:10:31,500 --> 01:10:34,370
Take this.

778
01:10:39,958 --> 01:10:40,998
If I fix the truck...

779
01:10:42,166 --> 01:10:44,166
If I fix the truck, what then?

780
01:10:44,333 --> 01:10:45,213
How would I know?

781
01:10:48,041 --> 01:10:48,671
Wait, wait.

782
01:10:48,875 --> 01:10:50,245
If I fix the truck,

783
01:10:50,500 --> 01:10:51,870
what would I need then?

784
01:10:52,041 --> 01:10:53,461
Of course you'll need a permit.

785
01:10:53,625 --> 01:10:54,535
I need a permit?

786
01:10:56,708 --> 01:10:57,578
I need a permit.

787
01:10:58,916 --> 01:10:59,866
Don't look at me.

788
01:11:00,750 --> 01:11:01,960
It's too risky!

789
01:11:25,875 --> 01:11:27,365
Even if you fix the truck,

790
01:11:27,916 --> 01:11:29,956
how would you get past the Japanese guards?

791
01:11:30,833 --> 01:11:31,673
I don't know.

792
01:11:34,625 --> 01:11:36,075
I don't know how long

793
01:11:36,750 --> 01:11:38,250
the guards will stay here.

794
01:11:39,541 --> 01:11:42,001
But I want to get that truck started

795
01:11:42,166 --> 01:11:43,366
for when they leave.

796
01:11:43,583 --> 01:11:46,543
It seems that you know more than just drinking.

797
01:11:56,125 --> 01:11:57,955
I don't think she likes seeing us together.

798
01:11:58,125 --> 01:11:59,325
She has a crush on you.

799
01:11:59,500 --> 01:12:00,120
Really?

800
01:12:03,958 --> 01:12:05,368
You know, I was like her.

801
01:12:07,166 --> 01:12:07,746
Yeah?

802
01:12:10,000 --> 01:12:12,290
I was at a convent for six years.

803
01:12:17,083 --> 01:12:19,753
That's where you learned your English?

804
01:12:26,125 --> 01:12:26,865
What happened?

805
01:12:28,458 --> 01:12:31,118
Just another story of misfortune.

806
01:12:31,291 --> 01:12:34,001
It wouldn't interest a passerby like yourself.

807
01:12:34,875 --> 01:12:35,615
Yeah, it would.

808
01:12:36,625 --> 01:12:42,365
Tell me.

809
01:12:46,333 --> 01:12:48,793
I was never meant to be like this.

810
01:12:52,541 --> 01:12:53,461
Never mind.

811
01:12:55,583 --> 01:12:56,333
You know what?

812
01:12:57,166 --> 01:12:59,666
I was the best in my English class,

813
01:13:00,333 --> 01:13:02,213
but everyone used to mock me.

814
01:13:02,666 --> 01:13:04,786
They said I put on airs and graces

815
01:13:05,333 --> 01:13:09,043
and acted like I was the Queen of England.

816
01:13:11,666 --> 01:13:13,916
Well, that's not
what you were going to tell me, but...

817
01:13:15,083 --> 01:13:16,673
So... the Queen of England.

818
01:13:17,083 --> 01:13:18,173
You mean you're not?

819
01:13:18,750 --> 01:13:20,370
I thought... yeah.

820
01:13:22,583 --> 01:13:25,253
Like Shu, I too had a crush on someone.

821
01:13:25,958 --> 01:13:28,828
But he was a young, fresh-faced guy,

822
01:13:30,333 --> 01:13:32,543
got the most beautiful eyes,

823
01:13:34,666 --> 01:13:36,666
not a dirty, bearded man like you.

824
01:13:41,791 --> 01:13:42,711
OK.

825
01:14:37,458 --> 01:14:38,288
It's rotten.

826
01:14:41,333 --> 01:14:44,543
Sister.

827
01:14:45,750 --> 01:14:46,540
What are you saying?

828
01:14:47,500 --> 01:14:48,080
Sister...

829
01:14:48,875 --> 01:14:49,575
Hurry...

830
01:14:51,458 --> 01:14:52,248
Pu Sheng,

831
01:14:52,500 --> 01:14:53,580
I'm here.

832
01:14:55,125 --> 01:14:56,165
Thunder...

833
01:14:57,208 --> 01:14:58,288
What are you trying to say?

834
01:15:00,166 --> 01:15:02,246
Rain...

835
01:15:05,875 --> 01:15:06,915
What rain?

836
01:15:07,791 --> 01:15:09,621
It's death weeping for you.

837
01:15:11,166 --> 01:15:15,326
The wheat is drying outside...

838
01:15:17,041 --> 01:15:20,291
Don't let it get soaked.

839
01:16:16,333 --> 01:16:18,123
That was the soldier that the officer brought.

840
01:16:18,541 --> 01:16:19,871
I heard he was about our age.

841
01:16:20,583 --> 01:16:21,713
Which officer?

842
01:16:22,000 --> 01:16:23,670
The officer who saved us that day.

843
01:16:25,500 --> 01:16:27,500
He hid the soldier inside the cellar,

844
01:16:28,000 --> 01:16:29,540
and the women were taking care of him.

845
01:16:30,416 --> 01:16:32,826
Actually those women from the brothel...

846
01:16:33,500 --> 01:16:34,580
are not that bad.

847
01:16:36,291 --> 01:16:37,211
Where's Dou?

848
01:16:40,333 --> 01:16:41,543
Lan's missing too.

849
01:16:41,875 --> 01:16:42,665
Really?

850
01:16:43,416 --> 01:16:45,116
Haven't seen them for a while.

851
01:16:45,750 --> 01:16:46,870
Are they still in the cellar?

852
01:16:47,541 --> 01:16:48,791
Have you seen Dou?

853
01:16:55,791 --> 01:16:58,211
Dou and Lan got out.

854
01:16:58,833 --> 01:16:59,543
How?

855
01:16:59,708 --> 01:17:00,618
Where did they go?

856
01:17:00,916 --> 01:17:03,326
Dou insisted on getting pipa strings.

857
01:17:03,791 --> 01:17:05,671
She wanted to play the pipa for Pu Sheng.

858
01:17:06,125 --> 01:17:07,365
She said he had a hard life,

859
01:17:07,625 --> 01:17:08,865
and he was like her brother.

860
01:17:09,416 --> 01:17:11,826
She wanted to play something nice for him,

861
01:17:12,125 --> 01:17:13,535
but one string wasn't enough,

862
01:17:13,750 --> 01:17:15,460
she needed three more.

863
01:17:15,708 --> 01:17:16,418
What about Lan?

864
01:17:16,750 --> 01:17:17,580
