Mr. Kato.

1695
02:10:55,125 --> 02:10:56,575
But you promised to help.

1696
02:10:56,750 --> 02:10:57,420
Shut up!

1697
02:10:59,250 --> 02:11:01,120
The chief commander is in charge.

1698
02:11:01,458 --> 02:11:01,998
Look,

1699
02:11:02,833 --> 02:11:04,123
he sent troops just for this.

1700
02:11:04,708 --> 02:11:06,248
We can't do anything.

1701
02:11:07,791 --> 02:11:09,331
But we had a deal.

1702
02:11:10,208 --> 02:11:13,458
I have given you all of my valuables.

1703
02:11:13,833 --> 02:11:14,503
Mr. Kato.

1704
02:11:14,875 --> 02:11:16,615
Please, you promised!

1705
02:11:16,791 --> 02:11:18,791
When did I take your things?

1706
02:11:23,291 --> 02:11:25,961
That was for our military expenses.

1707
02:11:30,625 --> 02:11:31,705
Then I'm begging you,

1708
02:11:32,291 --> 02:11:33,791
please allow me to see

1709
02:11:34,291 --> 02:11:35,961
my daughter one last time.

1710
02:13:18,291 --> 02:13:20,921
I'm not a student. I won't go!

1711
02:13:21,083 --> 02:13:23,003
I won't go!

1712
02:13:23,375 --> 02:13:24,785
I'm not a student!

1713
02:13:26,916 --> 02:13:28,246
Isn't that your daughter?

1714
02:13:28,416 --> 02:13:29,246
What is she saying?

1715
02:13:29,750 --> 02:13:30,830
Why is she shouting?

1716
02:13:31,541 --> 02:13:35,541
I'm not a student!

1717
02:13:40,208 --> 02:13:42,788
I won't go!

1718
02:13:50,750 --> 02:13:52,540
Be gentle with her, she's just a girl.

1719
02:14:07,083 --> 02:14:08,623
You've seen your daughter.

1720
02:14:59,666 --> 02:15:00,166
Let's go.

1721
02:15:00,500 --> 02:15:01,170
Come on.

1722
02:15:19,916 --> 02:15:20,536
Shu.

1723
02:15:21,875 --> 02:15:22,615
Come here.

1724
02:15:25,291 --> 02:15:27,831
Your father is a good man.

1725
02:15:28,041 --> 02:15:28,871
We could never have done this...

1726
02:15:29,041 --> 02:15:30,041
without your father.

1727
02:15:30,458 --> 02:15:31,418
He's a good man.

1728
02:15:37,958 --> 02:15:38,918
Watch your legs.

1729
02:17:25,708 --> 02:17:26,618
John told me that his biggest regret

1730
02:17:27,291 --> 02:17:27,921
was that, because

1731
02:17:28,083 --> 02:17:29,963
we had to get out as quickly as possible,

1732
02:17:30,375 --> 02:17:32,325
he couldn't give my father a proper burial.

1733
02:18:02,125 --> 02:18:05,535
Is this good for me to go through?

1734
02:18:08,833 --> 02:18:09,793
What's on the truck?

1735
02:18:14,541 --> 02:18:16,121
Empty wine cases, but...

1736
02:18:16,708 --> 02:18:18,288
four of them are full. They are...

1737
02:18:18,458 --> 02:18:20,118
very good, very good.

1738
02:18:20,291 --> 02:18:20,871
Here.

1739
02:18:21,708 --> 02:18:22,998
You see, vintage.

1740
02:18:24,541 --> 02:18:25,501
If you would like some.

1741
02:18:27,000 --> 02:18:27,750
Open it.

1742
02:18:33,625 --> 02:18:34,285
These.

1743
02:18:35,708 --> 02:18:36,208
Take.

1744
02:19:18,250 --> 02:19:19,540
Until this day

1745
02:19:19,750 --> 02:19:21,670
I still don't know what happened

1746
02:19:21,833 --> 02:19:23,043
to the women of the Qin Huai River.

1747
02:19:23,625 --> 02:19:25,915
I never learned all of their names,

1748
02:19:26,750 --> 02:19:28,040
and never saw them

1749
02:19:28,208 --> 02:19:29,708
being taken away by the Japanese.

1750
02:19:30,083 --> 02:19:31,873
So, I always imagine...

1751
02:19:32,416 --> 02:19:33,246
I imagine myself standing

1752
02:19:33,416 --> 02:19:34,826
by the large round window,

1753
02:19:35,208 --> 02:19:36,618
watching them walk in once again.

